        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 7 at 3:28PM EDT by NWS Morristown TN</headline>
        <description>At 327 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Wartburg, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Oak Ridge, Kingston, Wartburg, Oliver Springs, Harriman, Oakdale,
Coalfield, Frozen Head State Park, Petros, and Dearmond.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
